# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

llama.cpp uses specialized chat template handlers for models whose Jinja templates
require non-standard prompt construction. The Mistral Instruct v0.3 format
(`<s>[INST] {user} [/INST] {assistant}</s>…`) needs a dedicated handler that
manually builds the prompt string by iterating over messages and prepending any
system message to the first user turn. No Jinja rendering is needed — just string
concatenation — so `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` is the right output format.

The Mistral v0.3 Jinja template contains `[INST]` / `[/INST]` markers but does
**not** contain `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` (used by Ministral 3). That combination is the
unique signature for detection.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `common/chat.cpp` | All changes go here; no other file is modified |
| `common/chat.h` | Read-only reference; `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` already exists |

---

